Quantium Univerity Graduate		NAMEISPI:YES	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait						PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Quantium Univerity Graduate],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]		PREREGION:Nex				DESC:You graduated from one of Quantium's justly famous arcane academies, and the rigorous program of study has honed your mind. You gain a +2 trait bonus on concentration checks when casting arcane spells.																																																																																									SOURCEPAGE:p.14
# Nidal
Nidalese Shadowcaster			NAMEISPI:YES	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait						PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Nidalese Shadowcaster],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]			PREREGION:Nidal				DESC:You have studied with the feared shadowcasters of Nidal. Choose one spell with the shadow descriptor - from this point on, whenever you cast this spell, its effect manifest at +1 caster level.																															STACK:NO	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:NUMCHOICES=1|SPELLS|DESCRIPTOR=Shadow								BONUS:CASTERLEVEL|SPELL.%LIST|1																																				SOURCEPAGE:p.15
Uskwood Hunter				NAMEISPI:YES	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait						PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Uskwood Hunter],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]				PREREGION:Nidal				DESC:You have served the Umbral Court, discreetly following interlopers through the twilit city streets of Pangolais to pinpoint their locations for the authorities. You gain a +1 trait bonus on Stealth checks, and Stealth is always a class skill for you.																																																													BONUS:SKILL|Stealth|1|TYPE=Trait										CSKILL:Stealth			SOURCEPAGE:p.15
# Nirmathas
Fangwood Diplomat				NAMEISPI:YES	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait						PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Fangwood Diplomat],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]			PREREGION:Nirmathas			DESC:You've lived and worked among the disparate guerrilla groups of the Fangwood. You gain a +1 trait bonus on Diplomacy checks, and Diplomacy is always a class skill for you.																																																																										BONUS:SKILL|Diplomacy|1|TYPE=Trait										CSKILL:Diplomacy			SOURCEPAGE:p.15
Nirmathi Militia				NAMEISPI:YES	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait						PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Nirmathi Militia],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]			PREREGION:Nirmathas			DESC:You have served in one of the militia bands of Nirmathas, and have learned valuable skills. Select one of the following skills: Profession (soldier), Ride, or Survival. You gain a +1 trait bonus on that skill, and it is always a class skill for you.																					STACK:NO	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:NUMCHOICES=1|SKILLSNAMED|Profession (Soldier)|Ride|Survival																									BONUS:SKILL|%LIST|1|TYPE=Trait										CSKILL:%LIST			SOURCEPAGE:p.15
# Numeria
Technic Tinkerer							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait						PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Technic Tinkerer],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]			PREREGION:Numeria				DESC:You managed to uncover some lesser secrets of the Technic League, and have mastered a minor bit of magic. Choose a 0-level spell. You may cast that spell once per day as a spell-like ability. This is cast at your highest caster level gained; if you have no caster level, it functions at CL 1st.																																																																										SOURCEPAGE:p.16
Touched by the Sky						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait						PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Touched by the Sky],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]			PREREGION:Numeria				DESC:Somehow, you managed to retrieve a rare vial of fluid from a piece of crashed wreckage on the plains of Numeria. Before you could be caught with the contraband, you drank it. You now have the ability to stabilize a dying creature with a touch as a standard action.																																																																															SOURCEPAGE:p.16
# Osirion
Antiquities Smuggler						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait						PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Antiquities Smuggler],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]			PREREGION:Osirion				DESC:You have moved contraband relics from Osirion's elder days for years, and have learned some tricks. Choose one of the following skills: Appraise, Bluff, or Sleight of Hand. You gain a +1 trait bonus on that skill, and it is always a class skill for you.																				STACK:NO	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:NUMCHOICES=1|SKILLSNAMED|Appraise|Bluff|Sleight of Hand																										BONUS:SKILL|%LIST|1|TYPE=Trait										CSKILL:%LIST			SOURCEPAGE:p.16
Osirionologist							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait						PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Osirionologist],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]				PREREGION:Osirion				DESC:You have studied the history of ancient Osirion, and may have even ventured inside one of the great pyramids. You gain a +1 trait bonus on Knowledge (engineering) and Knowledge (history) checks, and one of them is always a class skill for you. In addition, you may choose Ancient Osiriani as one of your bonus languages.									STACK:NO	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:NUMCHOICES=1|SKILLSNAMED|Knowledge (Engineering)|Knowledge (History)																								BONUS:SKILL|Knowledge (Engineering),Knowledge (History)|1|TYPE=Trait				CSKILL:%LIST			SOURCEPAGE:p.16
# Qadira
Genie-Caller							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait						PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Genie-Caller],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]				PREREGION:Qadira				DESC:Your exploration of the magic for calling genies has increased your overall aptitude for summoning. Once per day, you may cast one Conjuration (Summoning) spell as if your caster level were 2 higher than normal.																																																																																							SOURCEPAGE:p.17
Rider of Paresh							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait	PREFEAT:1,Mounted Combat	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Rider of Paresh],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]				PREREGION:Qadira				DESC:You call the Plains of Paresh home, whether you were born among the plains' tribes or in the glittering towers of Katheer. The horses are your kin. When mounted and making a charge, your mount's speed is increased by 10 feet. You must have the Mounted Combat feat to take this trait.																																																																											SOURCEPAGE:p.17
# Rahadoum
Rahadoumi Cultist				NAMEISPI:YES	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait						PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Rahadoumi Cultist],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]			PREREGION:Rahadoum			DESC:You're a secret member of a forbidden faith in Rahadoum. You have learned to hide your beliefs and how to identify others of your faith. You gain a +5 trait bonus on Bluff checks to receive secret messages, and a +5 trait bonus on Sense Motive checks to intercept secret messages from others of your faith.																																																																								SOURCEPAGE:p.17
Rahadoumi Disbeliever			NAMEISPI:YES	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait						PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Rahadoumi Disbeliever],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]			PREREGION:Rahadoum			DESC:As a Rahadoumi who rejects covenants with gods, your belief is strong enough to repel divine spells. You gain a +2 trait bonus on saving throws against divine spells, but you must make a saving throw even when that magic is beneficial to you.																																																																																		SOURCEPAGE:p.17	ASPECT:SaveBonus|+2 trait bonus vs. divine spells
# Razmiran
Acolyte of Razmir				NAMEISPI:YES	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait						PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Acolyte of Razmir],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]			PREREGION:Razmiran			DESC:You are an adherent of the Razmiri faith, or once were and have since renounced it. You gain a +1 trait bonus on Knowledge (local) and Knowledge (religion) checks, and one of these skills is always a class skill for you. This bonus increases to +2 when dealing with specifics of the Razmiri faith.													STACK:NO	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:NUMCHOICES=1|SKILLSNAMED|Knowledge (Local)|Knowledge (Religion)																									BONUS:SKILL|Knowledge (Local),Knowledge (Religion)|1|TYPE=Trait					CSKILL:%LIST			SOURCEPAGE:p.18
Soldier of the Faith						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait						PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Soldier of the Faith],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]			PREREGION:Razmiran			DESC:You have served Razmir as a faithful enforcer, or upon one of the "faith barges" plying the waters of Lake Encarthan, and have learned the enforcement techniques of Razmiran. You gain a +1 trait bonus on Intimidate checks, and Intimidate is always a class skill for you.																																																										BONUS:SKILL|Intimidate|1|TYPE=Trait										CSKILL:Intimidate			SOURCEPAGE:p.18
# River Kingdoms
Bandit								CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait						PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Bandit],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]					PREREGION:River Kingdoms		DESC:Since you were young, you've been a member of one River Kingdoms bandit gang or another. Choose one of the following skills: Escape Artist, Intimidate, or Stealth. You gain a +1 trait bonus on that skill, and it is always a class skill for you.																						STACK:NO	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:NUMCHOICES=1|SKILLSNAMED|Escape Artist|Intimidate|Stealth																										BONUS:SKILL|%LIST|1|TYPE=Trait										CSKILL:%LIST			SOURCEPAGE:p.18
Riverfolk								CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait						PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Riverfolk],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]					PREREGION:River Kingdoms		DESC:You've grown up on the tributaries of the Sellen River system, and are as comfortable on boats as on land. You gain a +2 trait bonus on Profession (sailor) checks and any skill checks involving rope use.																																																																					BONUS:SKILL|Profession (Sailor)|1|TYPE=Trait													SOURCEPAGE:p.18
# Sargava
Jungle Guide							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait						PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Jungle Guide],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]				PREREGION:Sargava				DESC:You've made your living outfitting and guiding expeditions deep into the Mwangi interior in search of ancient ruins and lost cities. You gain a +1 trait bonus on Handle Animal checks, and a +1 trait bonus on Survival checks in jungle terrain. One of these skills is a class skill for you.															STACK:NO	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:NUMCHOICES=1|SKILLSNAMED|Handle Animal|Survival																											BONUS:SKILL|Handle Animal|1|TYPE=Trait									CSKILL:%LIST			SOURCEPAGE:p.19
Sargavan Guard							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait						PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Sargavan Guard],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]				PREREGION:Sargava				DESC:You served in the Sargavan Guard, either as a colonial sub-praetor or as a native Mwangi regular, and have grown accustomed to marching in hot temperatures while wearing armor. When you wear armor of any sort, reduce the armor check penalty by 1, to a minimum penalty of 0.																																																																													SOURCEPAGE:p.19
# Shackles
Shackles Seafarer							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait						PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Shackles Seafarer],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]			PREREGION:Shackles			DESC:You're familiar with the treacherous coastlines, currents, and tides of the Shackles, and can use that knowledge anywhere. You gain a +1 trait bonus on Knowledge (nature) and Knowledge (geography) checks while on the ocean. You also gain a +1 trait bonus on Swim checks, and Swim is always a class skill for you.																																																			BONUS:SKILL|Swim|1|TYPE=Trait											CSKILL:Swim				SOURCEPAGE:p.19
Stormrunner								CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait						PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Stormrunner],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]				PREREGION:Shackles			DESC:You have sailed on some of the roughest seas on Golarion, and have skirted the Eye of Abendego. You're accustomed to the pitch and yaw of sailing vessels, even in a storm, and gain a +2 trait bonus on Acrobatics checks to keep your footing on uneven ground or unsteady surfaces.																																																																												SOURCEPAGE:p.19
# Sodden Lands
Abendego Spellpiercer			NAMEISPI:YES	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait						PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Abendego Spellpiercer],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]			PREREGION:Sodden Lands			DESC:You have spent time in the gales of the perpetual hurricane, and can cast spells even when battered by the elements. You gain a +2 trait  bonus on concentration checks when spellcasting.																																																																																												SOURCEPAGE:p.20
Oagaon Diver				NAMEISPI:YES	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait						PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Oagaon Diver],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]				PREREGION:Sodden Lands			DESC:You know how to operate the diving bells of Oagon at the mouth of the Black Flow. You've dived the streets of sunken Lirgen yourself, and you know what to expect. You gain a +1 trait bonus on Swim checks, and Swim is always a class skill for you.																																																														BONUS:SKILL|Swim|1|TYPE=Trait											CSKILL:Swim				SOURCEPAGE:p.20
# Steaming Sea
Hermean Paragon				NAMEISPI:YES	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait						PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Hermean Paragon],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]				PREREGION:Steaming Sea			DESC:You are a product of Hermea's breeding programs - either your parents were chosen to be citizens, or you were, but later failed to live up to the island's high standards. Whatever the case, you are quicker than normal members of your race, and gain a +2 trait bonus on Initiative checks.																																																BONUS:COMBAT|INITIATIVE|2|TYPE=Trait																					SOURCEPAGE:p.20
Mordant Heritage				NAMEISPI:YES	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait						PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Mordant Heritage],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]			PREREGION:Steaming Sea			DESC:You have lived among the Mordant Spire elves and know their strange ways. You gain a +1 trait bonus on Swim checks and a +1 trait bonus on saving throws against enchantment effects.																																																																								BONUS:SKILL|Swim|1|TYPE=Trait																SOURCEPAGE:p.20	ASPECT:SaveBonus|+1 trait bonus vs. enchantment effects
# Taldor
Chivalrous								CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait						PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Chivalrous],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]				PREREGION:Taldor				DESC:You were raised on tales of heroic knights and benevolent wizards from Taldor's Golden Age, and try to emulate their great deeds. You gain a +1 trait bonus on Diplomacy and Knowledge (history) checks.																																																																					BONUS:SKILL|Diplomacy,Knowledge (History)|1|TYPE=Trait											SOURCEPAGE:p.21
Wealthy Dabler							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait						PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Wealthy Dabler],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]				PREREGION:Taldor				DESC:You study magic at one of Taldor's many social clubs, wowing your friends with your expertise in the simplest of magical exploits. Select two non-harmful arcane cantrips. You can cast these two cantrips once per day each (caster level 1st). If you have levels in a class that can cast these cantrips, your caster level for these cantrips is equal to that class level.																																																													SOURCEPAGE:p.21
# Thuvia
Desert Nomad							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait						PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Desert Nomad],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]				PREREGION:Thuvia				DESC:You were born and raised in the burning sands of Thuvia's desert interior. You gain a +4 trait bonus on any saving throws made to resist the effects of being in hot conditions, and a +1 trait bonus on all saving throws against fire effects.																																																																																			SOURCEPAGE:p.21	ASPECT:SaveBonus|+4 trait bonus vs. effects of being in hot conditions, +1 trait bonus vs. fire effects.
Thuvian Merchant				NAMEISPI:YES	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait						PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Thuvian Merchant],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]			PREREGION:Thuvia				DESC:You have traveled the great circular trade route around Thuvia, following the sale of the sun orchid elixir from city to city, and are used to haggling with foreigners. You gain a +1 trait bonus on Appraise, Bluff, and Sense Motive checks made for business deals and transactions.																																																																												SOURCEPAGE:p.21
# Ustalav
Superstitious Ward						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait						PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Superstitious Ward],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]			PREREGION:Ustalav				DESC:You're not frightened of the old wives' tales of vampires and ghosts, and though you try to avoid the undead, you've learned how to deal with them. You may cast disrupt undead once per day as a spell-like ability. This is cast at your highest caster level gained; if you have no caster level, it functions at CL 1st.																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.22
Ustalavic Noble				NAMEISPI:YES	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait						PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Ustalavic Noble],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]				PREREGION:Ustalav				DESC:You come from an aristocratic family, though your family has long since lost any power or prestige it once had. You gain a +1 trait bonus on Diplomacy and Knowledge (nobility) checks. In addition, your starting money is increased by 100 gp - your "birthright," such as it is.																																																																													SOURCEPAGE:p.22
# Varisia
Shoanti Tribesman				NAMEISPI:YES	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait						PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Shoanti Tribesman],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]			PREREGION:Varisia				DESC:You were born or adopted into a Shoanti tribe. Choose one of the following skills: Climb, Survival, or Swim. You gain a +1 trait bonus on this skill, and it is always a class skill for you.																															STACK:NO	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:NUMCHOICES=1|SKILLSNAMED|Climb|Survival|Swim																												BONUS:SKILL|%LIST|1|TYPE=Trait										CSKILL:%LIST			SOURCEPAGE:p.22
